<div class = "news">
    <h2> Today - The spicy soup </h2>
    <p> In the school canteen was served a soup to a student in 11-th grade. He claims that this soup was an ordinary pepper soup served by the school. 
        But there was a twist!It was hotter than the pepper used to make it!
        The student said that he felt like his mouth was on fire and that he had to drink a lot of water to cool it down. 
        He also said that the soup was so spicy that it made him sweat and cry and even made his nose run.
        The school administration has not yet commented on the incident, but they have promised to investigate the matter and take appropriate action if necessary. </p>
    <p> The recipe for the spicy soup is as follows: 
        <ul>
            <li> 1 liter of water </li>
            <li> 1 tablespoon of pepper </li>
            <li> 2 teaspoons of salt </li>
            <li> 1 tablespoon of oil </li>
            <li> 1 clove of garlic </li>
            <li> 1 tomato  </li>

        </ul>
    </p>
        <img class = "news-image" src = "spicy-soup (1).jpg" alt = "spicy soup" title = "SPICY SOUP">
    <p>By words of the cook, he said that he mistook the amount of pepper for the amount of salt. 
        He said that he accidentally added 2 tablespoons of pepper instead of 2 teaspoons of salt, which made the soup extremely spicy.
        The cook also said that he did not realize his mistake until the student complained about the soup.
        He apologized for the incident and said that he will be more careful in the future when preparing food.

    </p>
